{
  "texts": [
    "10 The function Circulant(x, y): {0, 1} n-1 Г— {0, 1} n вҶ’ {0, 1} m is implemented by:1.",
    "Set x вҖІ = [x, 0] вҲҲ {0, 1} n, where [,] denotes concatenation (i.e., x вҖІ n-1 = 0).",
    "Then,Circulant(x, y) = circ(x вҖІ)y 0:m-1, (23)where the matrix-vector multiplication circ(x вҖІ)y is taken mod 2 (in each component of the resulting vector) and the subscript 0: m -1 denotes the first m elements of the vector.",
    "The term circ(x вҖІ) is the n Г— n circulant matrix generated byx вҖІ = x вҖІ 0,... x вҖІ n-1, circ(x вҖІ) = пЈ® пЈҜ пЈҜ пЈҜ пЈҜ пЈ° x вҖІ 0 x вҖІ 1 x вҖІ 2... x вҖІ n-2 x вҖІ n-1 x вҖІ n-1 x вҖІ 0 x вҖІ 1 x вҖІ 2... x вҖІ n-2............ x вҖІ 1 x вҖІ 2 x вҖІ 3... x вҖІ n-1 x вҖІ 0 пЈ№ пЈә пЈә пЈә пЈә пЈ», (24)Using the result in the Appendix of [18], the function in Definition 9 can be implemented in O(n log n) computation time.",
    "m вүӨ k 1 + 2 log 2 (Пө)."
